# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of approximately 19 building blocks arranged in multiple layers. The structure has 3 main sections:
1. A left section resembling a train engine with arches
2. A middle connecting section with tall green pillars
3. A right section resembling a gate or archway

## Spatial Relationships
- **Base layer**: Red arch blocks (1, 2) form the base of the left section, with yellow blocks (11) forming the base of the right section
- **Middle layer**: Contains blue cubes (4), red cubes (7), yellow semi-cylinders (14, 16), green blocks of various shapes, and orange blocks
- **Top layer**: Features yellow tall blocks (12, 13) and a long yellow horizontal block spanning the right section

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on my analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:

1. Red arch block (index 1) - Used twice in the base of the left section
2. Red arch/cutout block (index 2) - Used once in the left section
3. Red arch/cutout block (index 3) - Used once in the left section
4. Blue cube (index 4) - Used twice (once in left section, once in right section)
5. Green cube (index 5) - Used twice (in left and middle sections)
6. Orange cube (index 6) - Used once in the middle section
7. Red cube (index 7) - Used twice (in both left and right sections)
8. Green horizontal block (index 8) - Used once in the middle section
9. Green vertical block (index 9) - Used once in the right section
10. Green vertical block (index 10) - Used once in the right section
11. Yellow horizontal block (index 11) - Used twice (as base and top of right section)
12. Yellow vertical block (index 12) - Used twice in the left section
13. Yellow vertical block (index 13) - Used once in the left section
14. Yellow semi-cylinder (index 14) - Used twice in the left section
15. Yellow cylinder (index 15) - Not used
16. Yellow wedge/half cylinder (index 16) - Not used (actually I see it is used in the assembly)
